content.detailedDescription:
Virginia beach, va - on the evening of 3/9/2015 around 8:50pm upon leaving the hair cuttery at brenneman farms marketplace, i filmed these pulsating red/orange orbs in the night sky. 

as i walked to my car, i looked up and noticed a number of pulsating orbs directly over head. at first i thought they might be drones or chinese lanterns. it took me a moment to get my phone camera rolling, at which point the largest group of orbs had faded out into the ne sky. the orbs were moving from the sw horizon, in procession, gradually gaining altitude until they simply faded out in the ne sky. each orb faded out in the same location. as the orbs faded their diameter gradually decreased. the orbs made no sound and never changed shape, with the exception of decreasing in diameter. in total, i would estimate having viewed 10+ orbs over a period of five minutes. 

there were two other witnesses in a car nearby. they pulled up next to me as the sighting ended and can be heard in the background. one lady believed the orbs might be drones. this is a possibility as there are numerous military facilities nearby.
content.summary: Multiple pulsating red-orange orbs ascending sw to ne in procession and then disappearing.

content.detailedDescription: Last night around 10:30 or 11 pm my father called me , my family and my girlfriend outside. he pointed out a bizarre looking star like object above an apartment conplex. he asked if that looked strange to us . realizing that we have binoculars i quickly ran back inside and got them. through binoculars of 20/80 we could clearly see that this object was flashing colors at a rapid pace. i watched it long enough to memorize the lightime order as white, red, blue, green,yellow. me and my little brother ran to the other side of the complex it was above to try and get a better look, there wasn't much of a difference in what we could see from our new spot. however when we turned to walk back to our apartment my little brother pointed and said "is that another one?" i looked through the binoculars and to my amazement there hovering above our complex was another object just like the first. we  called our dad over to look at our discovery. at the same time my girlfriend said to me "that right there is a plane right ?" my little brother answerved quickly "no a plane doesn't fly without lights" we sat there bewildered as a triangular object raced across the sky where it flew to the object over our complex and dissappeared. before we all went back inside we counted 4 orbs in the night sky all like the first. all changing colors and hovering silently. i went back out about 20 minutes later to see if they were still there, i saw what i thought was a plane at first racing back from over our complex towards the original orb we spotted. through binoculars i saw from what i believe to be a side view of the craft at first.  it was triangular in shape with a red light in the back, a blue in front, and two white lights in between. it flew right over me and on the underside where three white lights. one on each point. my heart sank, i had no ideal what i just looked at. i ran back inside to tell my father. when we returned outside every object we saw that night was gone without a trace.
content.summary: Sphere like objects in night sky.  through binoculars were rapidly changing colors and flashing.  a triangle was also witnessed flying low

content.detailedDescription:
Me and my children were driving on okeechobee road towards se 4 st, when my son pointed out that there was something in the sky. i looked and saw an airplane, i turned to him and said " ok i see the airplane too, (he's eight years old) he screamed at me again and said no look higher and that's when i saw an oval dome shaped aircraft with fire coming out towards the back of the craft. i could not believe my eyes so i started slowing down the speed of the car to get a better look at it.. the driver in back of me wasn't to happy and started to pass me on the right hand side, when she did, she saw me and my children looking  at the sky and she also saw the object we both started slowing down traffic trying to figure out what it was. it kept flying down okeechobee with fire and smoke exiting the back of the craft, until it made an abrupt turn right and started going down 8 ave east of hialeah. i kept following it myself and four other cars that were trying to get it on their cell phone cameras, but as i was looking at the fire and smoke had already stopped and all of sudden disappeared, like they turned a switch so we couldn't see it anymore. my kids and i were excited but scared my son kept asking me "what does this mean??" i said... i don't know.

ever since then i have found some footage that looks exactly like what i saw in youtube, under ufo flying over miami.
content.summary: I was driving on okeechobee rd when a dome looking craft was almost above us,

content.detailedDescription:
In july of 1982 myself, my brother and my brother's friend climbed to summit of mount albert edward on northern vancouver island (vancouver canada). returned to our camp about 4:30 or five pm. rested, built fire ate our dinner. the night sky was incredibly clear, lots of stars. we were standing, talking and  enjoying the night sky when i asked my brother's friend gregg if he had ever
seen anything strange when hiking alone (he was a high school science teacher who often went on long solo hiking trips in canadian wilds).   he answered "not until now." he pointed to northeast.
moving very slowly on a level path (east to west) at a fair distance away was a blue and white light 
it looked to me to just be aviation running lights. i thought it was probably a plane. the longer i watched i realized the lights weren't blinking or strobing. gregg though the lights strange and said
commercial air traffic was routed much further south to seattle tacoma and vancouver airports.
as we continued to watch it seemed as though the lights deviated from their patch and started moving more south than west, which brought it closer to us. the lights got bigger but we still could
not hear a sound associated to the lights. when the lights got closet it's path changed again. it was closer, still to our right (northeast) but now a parallel path to its first identified path. as it got closer to us the lights began to identify a shape. moving still closer the shape became more defined. it was saucer shaped with upside down smaller bowl on top, the saucer's "skirt" and a smaller bowl underneath. the skirt portion of the saucer looked to to over hang the bottom of the object.The surface of the object looked to be smooth and yellowish white finish. the underneath looked to have
attached structure three large dark boxes arranged in a triangle. when it passed directly in front of us a red blinking light came on. then the surface of the object started changing color. the white surface gradually started changing to a turquoise blue as if someone was pouring paint at the dome top and it was running down over the rest of the object. soon the turquoise color began to shift to a much darker blue. the object started moving a little faster and the blue surface color changed again to a smooth metallic stainless steal grey. it continued west and looked to accelerate on a path that took it back to its original path. when the object became just a group of red, blue and whites lights the object stopped, justing hanging in the air  (now to our north west) it hung there for a minute or more began to accelerate very fast as it got faster it started to zig-zag at an incredible speed then it stopped dead. lingered a minute it then shot straight up and out of sight. i decided to finally report my experience because i'm getting old and wanted to tell someone else about what happen back in 1982. i've told some friends and family but they either think i'm crazy or have a way too active imagination. sometimes i regret ever having told anyone.

all i can say now is that i know what i saw. maybe i'm having doubts but it would be nice to know that someone else had a similar experience.
content.flightPath: Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Camped with brother and his friend base of mount albert edward vancouver island, canada. object passed north in clear night sky

content.detailedDescription:
I was taking photos of the starry sky with a canon 1dx dslr and a 400mm lens.  i was taking long exposures (2 seconds each) to allow the faint stars to show up.  i noticed a dark shadow on one of the photos on the screen, and took more photos.  the next photo showed the same object, but it had moved, and appeared to be moving in a curved path.  i kept shooting, but the object did not appear in any more photos.
i was using a professional tripod, and the camera was not moved between any of the shots.  the two shots that contained the dark spot were taken within a few seconds of each other.  

i have no idea what this could be, but i can tell you a few things that it is not.  it is not something on the lens, because it would be so blurred as to not be visible.  the focus was set at infinity, and anything closer than a couple hundred feet would be so blurry that it would not be noticeable at all.  

it is not anything on the lens, because with this lens, and set at infinity, i can place one finger on the lens and you will not see any shadow. virtually the entire image gets a bit darker, as the finger is so out of focus.  

if the spot did not move, it could be claimed that it was dust on the sensor itself, but dust on the sensor does not show up for two photos, and move on it's own while the camera is on a tripod not moving, and then disappear.  i've had dust on the sensor plenty of times.  once it shows up, it stays there until you clean it off, and it never moves.

the object appears to be either standing still or moving very slowly across the field of view, so this eliminates any kind of flying animal, at any height.  again, for the shadow to be in as much focus as it is in would require the object to be hundreds of feet away, and as such, much larger that any bird or bat.  

i could see a scenario where a helium balloon or two tied together might cause in image like this, but the apparent motion is not in a straight line, and with the almost non-existent wind, i can't imagine a balloon moving in what appears to be a curved flight path.  if it was gusty, i could see a balloon moving like this, but the slight breeze was only about 1-2 mph, and at times it was dead calm.

there was absolutely nothing visible to my naked eye, but given that this was a long exposure, i would not expect to be able to see the object, even if i were to be using binoculars.  

keep in mind that this was a 2 second long exposure, so there would be some motion blur on the object even if it was in perfect focus, if it moved at all during the exposure. 

i heard nothing, and never saw anything unusual with my eyes.  i took many more photos, but nothing anomalous showed up before or after these two. 

i am attaching the unedited raw files.  these are canon's raw format, so you might need to convert them to a dng or jpg, but i will leave that to you so that you know i have not edited these at all.
content.summary: Black shadow showed up in two different places on two photos when taking photos of the night sky.

content.detailedDescription:
I was at dufferin islands between chippawa and niagara falls ontario waiting for clouds to clear to take some drone video.

i was looking up at the cloud cover and noticed 2 small black circles  ( could have been discs or orbs ) about 80-85 degrees up and to the south of dufferin islands making them between the islands and welland river moving in a straight line from west to east and not wavering with respect to each other at a very slow speed. the seemed as if they were connected or like jets flying in formation but very slowly. note that my vision is 20/20 on a recent eye exam

i watched for about 2 minutes trying to see if they were birds but didn't see wings, just 2 dark circles moving in a perfectly straight line at a perfectly steady speed, slightly offset to the wind direction.

while trying to get video they just disappeared. i scanned the sky for a minute or so but they didn't return.

i doubt anyone else saw them as i was looking at clouds for a break and were so high and small that one would have to be looking at that area to see them.

i could imagine they might be balloon's but those don't just instantly disappear while still in sight.
content.summary: 2 black circles under cloud cover floated along not changing position in relation to each other then disappeared

content.detailedDescription: Every year australians celebrate the anzac day dawn service. we gather to celebrate those servicemen and women lost at war. this event takes place just before dawn. today i was standing listening to the speeches when looking up to the horizon a very bright flashing light caught my eye.It was like a tripple strobing before it went out. after about 8-10 seconds it lit up once more only this time it wasn't as bright and it looked like a lighthouse light. gaining in intensity then dulling. the crowd around me heard me telling my two daughters and their school friends and then also began to follow its path. it was an extremely solem occasion so the environment was very quiet,the object gave no sound. we could see a dark sphere when the light was off and it moved slowly across the sky in a northwest direction. at one stage it gave out another bright burst of light before we lost sight of it. it was very high up. i'm not entirely sure of it's exact altitude but it was at a similar height of a commercial aircraft if not slightly lower and moving very slowly. when i first saw the light i knew it wasn't an aircraft because there were no navigation lights visible, there was no sound at all. i also have never seen a satellite this low and that emitted any light other than that of the suns reflection. we should've seen the sun reflecting off it at this time as the sun was rising behind it. even though we could see the dawns light on the horizon, given the objects altitude it would have been within the suns line of sight making it brighter. i'm not entirely sure on how many people witnessed this event? but i know the packed crowd around me had many looking up and pointing in bewilderment. i didn't get any photos of this event. but all i can say is that it looked like a black/charcoal sphere that seemed to fully light up before going dark again.
content.summary: We observed a dark sphere above the horizon that emitted an extremely bright strobing light at the anzac day dawn service. the light went out and randomly phazed on /off every 10 sec. there were roughly 2000 people at this service.

content.detailedDescription:
It was 6:45 in the morning i was headed out to take my boyfriend to work like i do everyday. i was standing outside looking at the morning sky when i saw something falling to the ground with a dust trail behind it. at first i thought it was a space rock of some kind.Big thought how cool it would be if it landed close enough for me to see it. then i dismissed that thought because it looked as though whatever it was was burning up before it reach the ground. then it stopped right above the big tree across the street and i could see it was a ball. a round sphere that looked like pictures we see of the earth divided into three layers. this ball had three layers all spinning. the colors were red, orange,blue and yellow. the outside was metalic. i thought to myself this isn't glowing or hot but the colors make me think of fire. it hovered there until the dust trail caught up to it then in shrunk smaller and smaller.Until it vanished
in the months before i witnessed 5 black helicopters and a week before i saw a black object the size of a building guide across the houses after a tornado pass through.

content.detailedDescription:
I was returning home after spending time in west phoenix and found myself turning onto southbound i-17 at the thunderbird ave. onramp.  this was at approximately 9:28pm arizona time on saturday april 23, 2016.

quickly after entering the freeway i had noticed what looked like helicopter lights and the helicopter was hovering.  it looked rather high in the sky and it was of course a dark night so i was unable to classify the craft, other than observing the lights at this point, and its unusually high position in the sky over the n, nw sky of phoenix.

next i observed (of course this is all while i'm driving on the freeway) a very dim green light descend from this craft.  as in falling from the hovering craft.  it appeared to fall more than 100 ft.  then the green light stopped in mid fall.  and appeared to hover below the original craft.  i could tell the craft above was moving westward because the two no longer seemed to line up in a straight line.  after about 20 seconds, that's when things became interesting.  the green light that had been hovering after falling instantly turned into a much larger object that i only could describe as a bloated double stuff oreo cookie.  it was impossible to see the top and bottom of this craft as it was black against the night sky.  the remarkable (and visual part of this siting) was the pale white center of the craft.  it did not emit light but rather looked like light was reflecting off of it.  pale white, not too terribly bright.  it appeared right from the green light that had fallen and hovered from the original craft (bright lights, strobing, moving).

keeping in mind, i was able to see this "bloated oreo double stuff shaped" craft for what seemed like a minute or two while driving.  i wished i had pulled over, but again i was on the freeway.  i was hoping there would be many other sightings and we could figure out what this was.  it indeed was a ufo, if it was a hoax it was superb!

if you have any information which might clarify this siting, please do not hesitate to contact me at my information provided.
content.summary: Observed a dim green light descending from what looked like help lights.  green light turned into hovering craft after stopping mid-air

content.detailedDescription: I got out of my car and checked the mail.  for some reason i noticed movement in the sky.  black birds were attacking a black box flying slowly above the neighborhood the object then flashed red and then black and ascended above the birds.  the red and black were not lights but rather as though it was red on one side and black on the other.  it was obviously a rectangular box and by the size of the birds id say 5 feet long.  it made no noise like a retail drone does (my neighbor has one its very annoying).  this was silent.  as it began to disappear behind the trees moving off to the se i realized there is a bridge over a railroad a few streets away that looks over most of the city so i hopped in my car and began to follow it.  just as i reached the bridge it just disappeared and from the west came a helicopter (black).  the show was over.  this is the oddest thing ive seen and in the middle of the day.  i stood for about eight minutes watching it at its lowest stunned just stunned as i quickly ruled out all the possibilities.  this was not a fuzzy lights in the dark ufo sighting.  the red and black is perplexing and the distance it traveled across the cityscape makes me think radio controlled retail drone is out of the question.  it really sped up after the bird business and covered a good distance when i last saw it as i was driving it was just a black dot in the distance...It was moving faster than before.  i wanted to report it because it was so odd.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Path with directional change

content.detailedDescription: Me and three other people were driving down a fairly empty road driving to a walmart when suddenly over a nearby group of houses i saw a row of five bluish lights standing perfectly still. at first i thought it was a formation of helicopters it looked like five helicopters right next to each other, but i realized this would be impossible as they would have to be literally glued to each other. it looked more like a solid object. there was no sound at all.  i would guess that it had an altitude of anywhere from about 300 to 1,000 feet, and a minimum size of 30-50 feet. as we kept driving we got closer to it and then it appeared more of a curved boomerang shape and there appeared to be a dark outline, it reminded me of a plane but it would have to have a very low altitude and would have to be hovering perfectly still for about a minute. then as we passed it it started moving suddenly at a constant pace, like it suddenly started gliding away in a perfectly straight line towards downtown lincoln. at this point the lights changed from five to only three and there was a green light and a red flashing one like a plane which i didn't notice before. one other person, the driver, also saw it and provided pretty much exactly the same details as i did. i tried to take a picture, but  i have an old phone with a terrible camera plus i was in a moving car. the driver stopped eventually, but at that point it was too far away and would have only appeared as a bright light in the sky, so i just didn't even bother at that point. the flashing red light makes me think it was a manmade aircraft, but the shape and arrangement of lights really looked strange and like nothing i have ever seen before both in real life or anywhere else.
content.summary: Five lights hovering over residential area, no sound, then suddenly started moving.

content.detailedDescription:
Witnessed a small single engine plane approximately over downtown phoenix, az., at about 9:30pm, sat. 4/23.  

at first i thought it was an airliner with engine troubles.  looked almost like a large meteor leaving behind a large orange tail about 100 feet in length, of showering sparks.  as the shower continued, a bright white ball of light descended from shower.

the plane was moving in a westerly direction and as it got closer i could make out the wing nav lights and the sound that it was a small engined plane.  the bright white ball descended slowly and then became an orange showery ball itself.  that then turned into a white ball again, descended lower and became an orange ball of sparks and then again turned into a white ball until finally reaching near ground level.

the plane made a slow clockwise circle towards me and then back over the downtown area before flying off to the south and out of sight.

ive never seen such a display before and wonder if you have seen other reports of same type.
content.summary: Small plane trailing orange showery fire tail dropping white orbs that also became glowing orange fireballs

content.detailedDescription: I was going to bed around 10:30-11:00 on saturday, april 23, 2016. i heard what i thought was someone knocking on my neighbors back door in the house behind us. as this is not normal, i looked out the window from my second story bedroom. i didn't see anyone in my neighbors yard so i was about to go back to bed when i saw what appeared to be a plane or helicopter in the distance traveling toward my house moving from the se to the nw. it just looked like a bright headlight from a plane. a little lower in the sky and brighter than what you'd normally see in the skies above my house but nothing alarming. however, after a few seconds of watching the light come toward my direction, it stopped and remained in one place. so, i thought it must be a helicopter. the light seemed pretty bright though and it did not have any flashing directional lights so i watched it for a while. it remained stationary for about a solid minute then started to move to the right. as it did, i saw a flash of red light which made me think i was watching a helicopter all this time. but the red flash was pretty bright and only red, no green flash followed as would be expected for a traditional aircraft. suddenly the entire light became completely red and remained a solid, glowing red color. it appeared to be a red oval shaped glowing light. it continued to move slowly to the right for a couple of seconds then made an abrupt 90 degree turn back in the direction from which it came and moved rapidly across the sky until i could no longer see it due to distance and trees in the foreground blocking the view. this most certainly was not a plane or helicopter. it made movements they are not capable of making and the speed at which this accelerated from a dead stop was pretty fast. i would appreciate if mufon or any other reporting agency can tell me if anyone else saw this. it is pretty frustrating when you are the only one that saw something so remarkable and you know for certain it was real but nobody else was there to corroborate your story. this is the second time i have seen something in the skies over brentwood and was alone when it occurred. please please please tell me if anyone else reported a similar sighting.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change
content.summary: White light that turned solid glowing red the reversed direction and flew out of sight

content.detailedDescription: I was on my back porch and i look up because i caught something moving in the sky. at first i couldn't believe it but i realized it was so real. it hovered around the craft made it look like it had no control and then they disappeared. i was shocked, scared, heart racing.
content.summary: 2 ufos hovered around an airplane and changed paths from sw to se and when fighter jets came they dissaperared

content.detailedDescription: We were driving to begin vacation. received phone call from doctor's office to pick up med so we turned onto a road off 500 block of ne 27th in moore, oklahoma in order to turn around to go to pharmacy. while waiting to make turn we saw a triangle just "hanging" in the sky to our one o'clock. all other clouds in sky were thin cirrus type, stretching from horizon to horizon. triangle appeared to be hiding in it's own cloud. see photo. we drove the 4 miles to pharmacy south on eastern street. i watched out the window as my husband drove. it never moved nor changed it's appearance. as soon as we parked i got my kindle out to take photographs. it was a bright sunny day. it was difficult to get the kindle to shoot directly west since it was about 4:15 p.M. and though sun wasn't directly in view, it isn't easy to work a kindle anyway photographing. since it was so bright, i have included a photo where i upped the contrast and turned down the brightness. other than that i didn't do anything else. after 30 minutes went by and nothing moved, i went inside pharmacy to get medicine. when i came out it was gone.
content.summary: Triangle clocked in cloud-like substance

content.detailedDescription:
While walking the dog i was looking straight east, and i saw a light travelling from southeast to northeast, it was followed by another and another. i kept looking and several more became visible all following, although not exactly single file. the first one i saw by itself, was followed by three in an angled triangle (i.E. not perfect triangle), and then there were more after that more or less in single file. there were 10 or 11 or so that i could see. they were low on the horizon, and were sometimes blocked by the tops of trees. 

i often see airplanes this time of night as they approach kansas city international airport from the east and these lights were definitely not planes, but they did travel quite a bit faster than airplanes i have seen on a similar flight path. 

there was no discernible sound heard - but if they had been planes, i definitely would have heard them as i have often seen planes coming from that direction and following a similar path. this was between 9:30 and 9:50 pm saturday april 23rd. (sorry not exact on the time because i was not wearing my watch and had forgotten to bring my phone with me). the sighting only lasted slightly over a minute or so.

during the short sighting, the lights pulsated and the colors changed between white, yellow and green and would dim and brighten, but not in unison.
content.summary: Several pulsating lights seen traveling from southeast to northeast, fairly low on the horizon. the lights pulsated and changed colors from white to yellow to green and dimmed and brightened (pulsated). the sighting only lasted about a minute.

content.detailedDescription: I was at work and first saw a hawk in the sky so i took out my camera taking a shot of the hawk. then this green orb emerged from the clouds below the hawk, and began traveling in a straight line path from the southeast to the northeast.The object appeared green in color with reflective smaller lights which changed position on the craft as it moved through the sky.I felt in shock during and then ill after this event. once it made it past me in its flight path it disappeared just northeast of my position.
content.summary: It was behind cloud cover and then traveled quickly on a straight line path

content.detailedDescription: The ufo was on the other side of the phone cables.  my cell phone camera caught it in mid flight.  it was traveling so fast it appeared to come out of the sky and then disappear back into the sky in the matter of maybe 2 seconds or less.
content.summary: Disc shaped ufo moved at lighting speed as it appeared out of the sky and then disappeared
